Sexual, domestic or family violence can happen to anyone, in any relationship. It is never ok. #1800RESPECT provides information, referrals, and counselling to anyone impacted, 24 hours a day, every day of the year. Visit https://t.co/FvWH1Y4R8z for more information.

How you respond to someone impacted by #violence makes a big difference. If you do not have training in this area, the best thing you can do is respond sensitively, and refer the person to a specialist service. Our website has more information.  https://t.co/EYcBAlOvQS

Recent media coverage detailing #sexualassault or #familyviolence can be a trigger for people who have experienced abuse. 1800RESPECT‚Äôs service is available to support anyone, 24/7. You can visit https://t.co/FvWH1Y4R8z or phone 1800737732. Share to let others know.

Did you know the #1800RESPECT website has information in 29 languages? You can find information including safety planning, and how to support someone impacted by #sexualassault and #domesticviolence. https://t.co/mLR6beRhVl

Visit the #news and media page on our website to read media releases and articles from #1800RESPECT, how and when to use our tagline, and how to get in touch for media enquiries.  https://t.co/zwc4JEVeLX

If you have experienced #sexualassault or #domesticviolence, it's important to know that support is available. #1800RESPECT hosts national service directory of support services. Find services in your area at https://t.co/SfnlWUgd6U or download the specially designed Daisy app.

What does #financialabuse feel like? Shame and humiliation and feelings of hopelessness and helplessness, these are really common when you're experiencing financial abuse. You are not alone and support is available. Contact 1800RESPECT on 1800 737 732. https://t.co/xtkP3EroA3

#1800RESPECT materials such as cards, stickers and pens for your community are available to order on our website. This helps raise awareness of our service, so they know where to reach out for confidential support for #sexualassault and #domesticviolence. https://t.co/F6V1KPw0Fk

1800RESPECT is Australia‚Äôs national #sexualassault, family and #domesticviolence support service. Anyone can contact us 24/7 for information, counselling and referrals via phone or webchat. Phone 1800 737 732 or visit our website. https://t.co/bcJlxNTsZX #1800respect

#1800RESPECT is at the front line of #sexualassault and #domesticviolence support services in #Australia. Anyone impacted by violence can contact our service, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. You can visit https://t.co/FvWH1Y4R8z or call 1800737732 to speak to a trained counsellor.

We invite you to subscribe to our Workers and Professionals newsletter. Updates on the #1800RESPECT service, #DVSA sector information, upcoming #conferences and more are delivered quarterly to your inbox. Sign up via our website. https://t.co/ZmQVSs9Gc7

#Stalking is when someone won't stop bothering you with unwanted contact or attention. It involves behaviour that aims to scare and control you and can be a form #violence and #abuse. Find out more on our website.  https://t.co/IuBGNwdFpt

@shorey24 @abc730 @nadiasdaly @jeff_kennett @beyondblue We are already wholly funded by the Australian Government under the National Plan. If you're unsure about any details about us, all info is on our website: https://t.co/PWjkc4PquR Many state and local services do lobby for additional funding in order to assist more people.

If you feel there is something not right about the way you are being treated, you can talk with one of our counsellors. They can help you understand what you have experienced, and support options. Learn more about the 1800RESPECT service in our FAQs. https://t.co/hOufJBOv2G

#1800RESPECT continues to operate during the #COVID19 health emergency, available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Call 1800 737 732, or if you feel it is safer to do so, contact us via web chat on our website at https://t.co/FvWH1Y4R8z. If you are in immediate danger, call 000.
